<p>HUMAN RIGHTS COUNCIL 
Second session 
Agenda item 2 
</p>
<p><b>IMPLEMENTATION OF GENERAL ASSEMBLY RESOLUTION 60/251 
OF 15 MARCH 2006 ENTITLED &#8220;HUMAN RIGHTS COUNCIL&#8221; 
</b></p>
<p><b>Canada:  draft decision 
</b></p>
<p><b>2006/&#8230;  Freedom of opinion and expression 
</b></p>
<p> The Human Rights Council, recalling Commission on Human Rights resolution 2005/38 
of 15 April 2005, decides to request the Special Rapporteur on the promotion and protection of 
the right to freedom of opinion and expression, with the support of the Office of the 
United Nations High Commissioner for Human Rights, to undertake a study on the issue of the 
security of journalists, in particular in situations of armed conflict, taking into account 
information provided by States and intergovernmental and non-governmental organizations, 
including national press associations. 
</p>
